        "success_criteria": "The probability that a structural or stratigraphic closure is present to contain at least one accumulation in the play area with minimum hydrocarbon volume or more",
        "description": "The probability that a valid trapping geometry (closure) is present at the correct stratigraphic level to contain at least one accumulation. This pillar assesses GEOMETRY ONLY — 4-way dip, 3-way fault-assisted, stratigraphic pinch-out, or combined traps. Seal capacity is NOT assessed here — it belongs in Retention.",
        "considerations": "Things to consider when assigning play closure risk:\n\n• Closure type: What is the trapping mechanism?\n\n• Seismic confidence: What is the structural confidence on the mapped closure?\n\n• Depth conversion uncertainty: Could velocity errors open or close the structure?\n\n• ⚠️ Do NOT assess seal here. Seal capacity belongs in the Retention pillar.",
